{{Infobox video game | title = AirAttack | image = AirAttack video game logo.jpeg | caption = App store icon | developer = [[Art In Games]] | publisher = Art In Games | platforms = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | released = July 15, 2010 | genre = [[Action video game|Action]] | modes = }}
'''''AirAttack''''' is a {{vgy|2010}} [[action video game]] developed and published by Slovak studio Art In Games.
==Design== Touch Arcade notes "AirAttack departs from the traditional 2D platform of vertical shoot-em-ups and opts for a fully realistic 3D world", creating a point of difference from other similar games of this nature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2010/07/19/air-attack-review-a-punchy-3d-shmup-spectacle/|title='Air Attack' Review -- A Punchy 3D Shmup Spectacle|date=19 July 2010|publisher=}}</ref>
==Gameplay== ''AirAttack'' is an action video game played from top-down perspective and three-dimentional environment. At the beginning of the game, the player starts with three planes, resembling the F4U Corsair, P-38 Lightning and P-40 Tigershark. They must choose one from the three and start their fight. The latter planes also use flamethrower and fireball. A flamethrower is used to burn all types of enemies while the fireball serves the plane as deflection from crashing into another planes with swift pivotal circulation. The player's plane has a primary weapon that fires continuously at a constant velocity that can attack aerial enemies, land enemies except the train, and certain buildings. The plane is manipulated by moving it along screen, possibly using mouse, tilting the device, joypad and relative touch (manual input sensitivity). Double tapping the screen drops a bomb that can destroy land enemies and buildings in order to collect coins. Shop also appears throughout the level. Player can enter it to buy gadgets such as homing rockets, super rockets, turrets, shields, side planes, lightnings, bombs that can destroy wider area, extra lifes, cannons, and timewraps (provides [[slow motion]] technique).
== Reception == {{Video game reviews | title = ''AirAttack'' | GR = 78.75%<ref name="GRiOS">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/iphone/999153-airattack/index.html |title=AirAttack (iOS) |publisher=[[GameRankings]] |date= |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> | MC = 84/100<ref name="MCiOS">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/airattack |title=AirAttack (iOS) |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |date= |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> | rev1= ''[[148 Apps]]'' | rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name="148 Apps">{{cite web|url=http://www.148apps.com/reviews/airattack-review-2/ |title=AirAttack Review |publisher=148 Apps |date=August 27, 2010 |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> | rev2= [[App Safari]] | rev2Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appsafari.com/games/12533/airattack/|title=AirAttack iPhone game app review - AppSafari|work=appsafari.com}}</ref> | rev3= ''AppSpy'' | rev3Score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref name="AppSpy">{{cite web|url=http://www.appspy.com/review/4183/airattack |title=AirAttack Review |publisher=AppSpy |date=July 16, 2010 |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> | rev4= [[Common Sense Media]] | rev4Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/app-reviews/airattack-hd|title=AirAttack HD|work=commonsensemedia.org}}</ref> | rev5= [[Multiplayer.it]] | rev5Score = 9/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://multiplayer.it/recensioni/79457-airattack-fuoco-sopra-i-cieli-di-berlino.html|title=AirAttack|author=Giovanni Polito|date=17 August 2010|work=Multiplayer.it}}</ref> | rev6= No dPad | rev6Score = Must Have (the highest grade)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nodpad.com/2010/08/02/air-attack-review-its-da-bomb/|title=Air Attack Review: It’s Da Bomb « No DPad - The latest in iPhone and iPod Touch gaming reviews, previews and news.|work=nodpad.com}}</ref> | rev7= PadGadget | rev7Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.padgadget.com/2010/08/21/air-attack-hd-app-review/|title=Air Attack HD – App Review|author=PadGadget|work=padgadget.com}}</ref> | rev8= ''[[Pocket Gamer]]'' | rev8Score = 6/10<ref name="Pocket Gamer">{{cite web|url=http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/iPhone/AirAttack/review.asp?c=22318 |title=AirAttack Review |publisher=[[Pocket Gamer]] |date=August 2, 2010 |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> | rev9= ''Slide to Play'' | rev9Score = 3/4<ref name="Slide To Play">{{cite web|url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/airattack-review/ |title=AirAttack Review |publisher=Slide To Play |date=July 26, 2010 |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> }}
The game received generally positive reviews from critics. Aggregating review website [[GameRankings]] provides an average rating of 78.75% based on 4 reviews,<ref name="GRiOS"/> whereas [[Metacritic]] provides an average rating of 84 out of 100 based off 6 reviews, meaning generally favorable reviews.<ref name="MCiOS"/>
== Sequel == ''[[AirAttack 2 - WW2 Airplanes Shooter|AirAttack 2]]'' is a 2015 action video game developed and published by Art In Games as the sequel to the original.
