==Reception==
''Missing Richard Simmons'' was met with mixed reviews from critics. [[Amanda Hess]] of the ''[[New York Times]]'' described the podcast as "morally suspect", whilst also stating it was an invasion of Simmons' privacy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/14/arts/missing-richard-simmons-podcast.html/|title= 'Missing Richard Simmons,' the Morally Suspect Podcast|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> Similar sentiments were raised by ''[[Rolling Stone]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/missing-richard-simmons-everything-you-need-to-know-w470516|title= 'Missing Richard Simmons' Podcast: Everything You Need to Know |accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> ''[[The Week]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theweek.com/articles/684751/no-problem-missing-richard-simmons-podcast-thats-problem|title=No one has a problem with the ''Missing Richard Simmons'' podcast, and that's a problem |accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> and [[Vox (website)|Vox]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2017/3/21/14978658/missing-richard-simmons-controversy|title=Missing Richard Simmons: how a podcast became an experiment in privacy invasion|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> amongst others. Despite this however, these critics would also mention the "instantly engaging" nature of the podcast,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/14/arts/missing-richard-simmons-podcast.html/|title= ‘Missing Richard Simmons,’ the Morally Suspect Podcast|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> with 
[[New York (magazine)|Vulture.com]] calling it "the strongest narrative podcast out there."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2017/03/missing-richard-simmons-podcast-review.html|title= ''Missing Richard Simmons'' Is a Brilliant Podcast – So Far|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref>

''Missing Richard Simmons'' proved popular with audiences, topping the iTunes podcast charts in the Australia, Canada, United Kingdom and United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/artists/podcast/first-look-media-pineapple-street-media-stitcher/podcasts/missing-richard-simmons/|title=iTunesCharts.net: Missing Richard Simmons|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref> In the United States, the podcast spent almost three weeks in the number one spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/us/artists/podcast/first-look-media-pineapple-street-media-stitcher/podcasts/missing-richard-simmons/|title=iTunesCharts.net: Missing Richard Simmons: American Chart Performance|accessdate=December 11, 2017 |language=English}}</ref>

